Remarks. The nymphal instars are similar, differing primarily in morphometric characters, and previously difficult or impossible to separate due to the absence of a taxonomic key. This work attempts to solve this problem by analyzing body features with morphometric comparisons of both adults and immatures ( Tables 1 & 2). The tube spittlebug attacks the jujube crop at the time of flowering (Fig. 69) and affected flowers are dried completely (Figs 71, 72) and heavy infestation can cause complete failure of the crop (
Prodhan et al. 2016
).
